  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-alias=\"gutenberg-content__content\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/t/tom-cruise/\" id=\"auto-tag_tom-cruise\" data-tag=\"tom-cruise\"\u003eTom Cruise\u003c/a\u003e is embracing the need for speed… but not of the “Top Gun” variety. \u003ca rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" data-id=\"https://x.com/TomCruise/status/1938644231125598217\" target=\"_blank\" data-type=\"link\" href=\"https://x.com/TomCruise/status/1938644231125598217\"\u003eOn X June 27\u003c/a\u003e, Cruise wrote a congratulatory message to producer Jerry Bruckheimer, who not only is the man behind this weekend’s box office hit “\u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/t/f1/\" id=\"auto-tag_f1\" data-tag=\"f1\"\u003eF1\u003c/a\u003e,” but also the Cruise-starring NASCAR \u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/t/film/\" id=\"auto-tag_film\" data-tag=\"film\"\u003efilm\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" data-id=\"https://www.indiewire.com/news/general-news/hans-zimmers-days-of-thunder-score-finally-coming-to-cd-t-bone-burnett-scoring-true-detective-92244/\" target=\"_blank\" data-type=\"link\" href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/news/general-news/hans-zimmers-days-of-thunder-score-finally-coming-to-cd-t-bone-burnett-scoring-true-detective-92244/\"\u003e“Days of Thunder”\u003c/a\u003e — released in theaters 35 years \u003cem\u003eto the day\u003c/em\u003e of the new \u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/t/brad-pitt/\" id=\"auto-tag_brad-pitt\" data-tag=\"brad-pitt\"\u003eBrad Pitt\u003c/a\u003e-led Formula One action drama.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“I always love the fun and adrenaline of a racing film,” Cruise wrote. “Today marks two racing milestones for my friend Jerry Bruckheimer, the release of ‘F1’ and the 35 year anniversary to the day of our collaboration with the great Tony Scott on ‘\u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/t/days-of-thunder/\" id=\"auto-tag_days-of-thunder\" data-tag=\"days-of-thunder\"\u003eDays of Thunder\u003c/a\u003e.\u0026#39;”\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv data-alias=\"cards__inner\" data-component=\"cards-related-content\" data-collapse-to-xs=\"false\" data-layout=\"inline\" data-size=\"md\" data-spacing=\"s-3\" data-cards-spacing=\"s0\"\u003e \u003cdiv data-alias=\"card__inner\" data-post-id=\"1235135798\" data-component=\"card\" data-has-background=\"false\" data-has-overlay=\"false\" data-layout-size=\"xs\" data-layout=\"sidebar\" data-main-alignment=\"s0\" data-main-spacing=\"s0\" data-media-position=\"\"\u003e\u003cfigure data-component=\"image\" data-alias=\"\" data-ratio=\"sixteenByNine\" data-round=\"false\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/news/general-news/henry-golding-crazy-rich-asians-series-could-drop-next-year-1235135798/\" title=\"\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"\" data-card-index=\"0\" data-post-id=\"1235135798\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/P101FCPF.jpg?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\" alt=\"Henry Golding at the 2025 Met Gala\" height=\"168\" width=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/P101FCPF.jpg?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=600%2C337 600w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/P101FCPF.jpg?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=125%2C70 125w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/P101FCPF.jpg?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=660%2C370 660w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/P101FCPF.jpg?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=50%2C28 50w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/P101FCPF.jpg?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=300%2C168 300w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/P101FCPF.jpg?w=300\u0026amp;h=168\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1200%2C675 1200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" loading=\