ttps://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=234,187 234w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=1000,800 1000w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=313,250 313w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=244,195 244w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=1160,928 1160w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=375,300 375w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=119,95 119w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=50,40 50w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=1200,960 1200w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=46,37 46w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=281,225 281w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=563,450 563w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=1125,900 1125w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=35,28 35w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=210,168 210w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=421,337 421w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=844,675 844w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=41,33 41w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=250,200 250w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=500,400 500w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=31,25 31w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=188,150 188w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=750,600 750w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=150,120 150w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=110,88 110w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=285,228 285w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=320,256 320w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=640,512 640w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=800,640 800w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=960,768 960w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/IMG_6117.jpg?resize=1280,1024 1280w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eOn the set of ‘Days of Thunder’\u003ccite\u003ephoto courtesy of Tom Cruise X\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“Incredible to look back on this film today, and congratulations to Jerry, Brad, Joe and the whole F1 team on their release,” Cruise added.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe comparisons between Cruise and Pitt’s action prowess was also made earlier this month at the “F1” premiere, when \u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/news/general-news/brad-pitt-wont-hang-his-ass-off-a-plane-for-tom-cruise-1235132660/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.indiewire.com/news/general-news/brad-pitt-wont-hang-his-ass-off-a-plane-for-tom-cruise-1235132660/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003ePitt responded to the suggestion\u003c/a\u003e that he star alongside his fellow box office champ in a “Mission: Impossible”-style thriller.\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“Well, I’m not gonna hang my ass off airplane shit like that,” he said in an interview \u003ca href=\"https://x.com/EOnlineAU/status/1933056677282025629\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://x.com/EOnlineAU/status/1933056677282025629\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003ewith E! News\u003c/a\u003e. “When he does something again that’s on the ground.”\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe pair have known one another for decades, and racing has helped define their friendship since the beginning — albeit in not quite as high stakes a venue. “He’s sweet,” Pitt said of Cruise. “Yeah, we did have our go-cart days back in the ’90s,” though he said that Cruise usually beat him on the go-cart track.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“F1” director Joseph Kosinski, who also led “Top Gun: Maverick” in 2022, said there is a possibility “Days of Thunder” could be woven into a future “F1” sequel. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e“Well, right now, [the sequel would] be Cole Trickle, who was [Cruise’s] ‘Days of Thunder’ character,” Kosinski told GQ (\u003ca href=\"https://movieweb.com/f1-director-teases-sequel-tom-cruise-days-of-thunder/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://movieweb.com/f1-director-teases-sequel-tom-cruise-days-of-thunder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\"\u003evia Movieweb\u003c/a\u003e). “We find out that he and [Brad Pitt’s] Sonny Hayes have a past. They were rivals at some point, maybe crossed paths… I heard about this epic go-kart battle on ‘Interview With the Vampire’ that Brad and Tom had, and who wouldn’t pay to see those two go head-to-head on the track?” \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003ePitt and Cruise \u003ca rel=\"noreferrer noopener nofollow\" data-id=\"https://collider.com/brad-pitt-tom-cruise-joseph-kosinski-ford-v-ferrari/\" target=\"_blank\" data-type=\"link\" href=\"https://collider.com/brad-pitt-tom-cruise-joseph-kosinski-ford-v-ferrari/\"\u003ealmost paired together\u003c/a\u003e in a racing drama based on the book “Go Like Hell” by A.J. Baime. In 2013, \u003ca href=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/brad-pitt-courted-tom-cruises-666348/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/brad-pitt-courted-tom-cruises-666348/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003eTHR reported\u003c/a\u003e that \u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/features/general/ford-v-ferrari-tom-cruise-brad-pitt-go-like-hell-1234576232/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.indiewire.com/features/general/ford-v-ferrari-tom-cruise-brad-pitt-go-like-hell-1234576232/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003ePitt and Cruise were in talks to star in that movie\u003c/a\u003e, which would take six more years to actually make it to the screen. Even before that, the project had been through several potential incarnations, with Pitt rumored to be on the casting list as early as 2009.\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn the end, neither would end up starring in the movie, and “Go Like Hell” was a title that eventually was scrapped, too. It instead became \u003ca href=\"https://www.indiewire.com/criticism/movies/ford-v-ferrari-review-matt-damon-christian-bale-1202170145/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.indiewire.com/criticism/movies/ford-v-ferrari-review-matt-damon-christian-bale-1202170145/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003e“Ford v. Ferrari,”\u003c/a\u003e starred Christian Bale and Matt Damon, netted four Oscar nominations (including Best Picture), and raked in over $225 million at the box office.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"819\" width=\"1024\" src=\"https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?w=650\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg 1350w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=300,240 300w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=1024,819 1024w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=125,100 125w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=600,480 600w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=234,187 234w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=1000,800 1000w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=313,250 313w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=244,195 244w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=1160,928 1160w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=375,300 375w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=119,95 119w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=50,40 50w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=1200,960 1200w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=46,37 46w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=281,225 281w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=563,450 563w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=1125,900 1125w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=35,28 35w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=210,168 210w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=421,337 421w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=844,675 844w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=41,33 41w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=250,200 250w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=500,400 500w, https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/GudrYOObYAACH7B.jpg?resize=31,25 31w, https://www.indiewire.c